<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-1483191/R-HSA-1483191>
        a       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0006656> , <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "<i>De novo</i> (Kennedy pathway) synthesis of phosphatidylcholine (PC) involves phosphorylation of choline (Cho) to phosphocholine (PCho) followed by condensing with cytidine triphosphate (CTP) to form CDP-choline (CDP-Cho). Diacylglycerol (DAG) and CDP-ETA together then form PC. Alternatively, PC is formed when phosphatidylethanolamine (PE) is methylated by phosphatidylethanolamine N-methyltransferase (PEMT) (Henneberry et al. 2002; Wright & McMaster 2002)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Synthesis of PC" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, Peter, 2025-08-13" , "Reviewed: Wakelam, Michael, 2012-05-14" , "Authored: Williams, MG, 2011-09-14" , "Edited: Williams, MG, 2011-08-12" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
                "2026-07-02" ;
        <http://purl.org/pav/providedBy>
                "https://reactome.org" ;
        <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref>
                "R-HSA-1483191" ;
